A major caveat in plume sampling is the sparseness of icy plume material. Cassini images, taken from very high solar phase angles (since the plume is invisible in reflected light), can be quite misleading because the plume is actually extremely tenuous. The current best estimates yield an average total emission rate for ice grains of about 20–25kg/s\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
