Successful penetration and the avoidance of destructive side loads relies on the vehicle having essentially zero angle of attack (i.e. vehicle axis and velocity vector aligned) and zero incidence (i.e. velocity aligned with the surface normal) to within ≤10∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
