Another solution, that would indeed provide sufficient power could be to place a nuclear reactor on the surface, close to the melting location. Obviously, the transport and operations of such infrastructure has significant challenges. Reactors do have space heritage, however only in Earth orbit (El-Genk 2009). In the former Soviet Union, “BUK” power systems with SiGe\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
